.TH CREATELANDSEAMAP 1 "2026-05-02" "smartmet-tools-grid" "SmartMet GRID Tools"
.SH NAME
createLandSeaMap \- generate a land/sea bitmap from GlobCover land\(hycover data
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B createLandSeaMap
.I coverDir
.I width
.I height
.I mapFile
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B createLandSeaMap
generates a packed bitmap that marks every pixel of an equirectangular
world map as land or sea, using the GlobCover land\(hycover dataset as the
source.
.PP
The bitmap covers the full globe (longitude
.RB \(lq \-180 \(rq..\(lq +180 \(rq,
latitude
.RB \(lq \-90 \(rq..\(lq +90 \(rq)
at a resolution of
.IR width " x " height
pixels. Each pixel is one bit; bits are packed eight per byte. Sea,
Caspian Sea and lake pixels are stored as zero, everything else as one.
The result is written to
.IR mapFile .
.PP
The generated bitmap is consumed at runtime by
.BR corbaDataServer (1)
and other components that need a fast land/sea lookup, for example to
implement landscape interpolation.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I coverDir
Path to a directory of GlobCover land\(hycover tiles, in the layout
expected by
.BR Fmi::LandCover .
.TP
.I width
Bitmap width in pixels.
.TP
.I height
Bitmap height in pixels.
.TP
.I mapFile
Output filename for the packed bitmap.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR corbaDataServer (1),
.BR corbaGridServer (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Finnish Meteorological Institute
.PP
